quran[14]{c,v,t}:
  2,197,"Let the Pilgrimage be made in the months already known: whoever therefore undertaketh the Pilgrimage therein, let him not know a woman, nor transgress, nor wrangle in the Pilgrimage. The good which ye do, God knoweth it. And provide for your journey; but the best provision is the fear of God: fear me, then, O men of understanding"
  2,198,"It shall be no crime in you if ye seek an increase from your Lord; and when ye pour swiftly on from Arafat, then remember God near the holy monument; and remember Him, because He hath guided you who before this were of those who went astray"
  2,199,"Then pass on quickly where the people quickly pass, and ask pardon of God, for God is Forgiving, Merciful"
  2,200,"And when ye have finished your holy rites, remember God as ye remember your own fathers, or with a yet more intense remembrance! Some men there are who say, \"O our Lord! give us our portion in this world:\" but such shall have no portion in the next life"
  2,201,"And some say, \"O our Lord! give us good in this world and good in the next, and keep us from the torment of the fire"
  2,202,"They shall have the lot which they have merited: and God is swift to reckon"
  2,203,"Bear God in mind during the stated days: but if any haste away in two days, it shall be no fault in him: And if any tarry longer, it shall be no fault in him, if he fear God. Fear God, then, and know that to Him shall ye be gathered"
  2,204,A man there is who surpriseth thee by his discourse concerning this life present. He taketh God to witness what is in his heart; yet is he the most zealous in opposing thee
  2,205,"And when he turneth his back on thee, he runneth through the land to enact disorders therein, and layeth waste the fields and flocks: but God loveth not the disorder"
  2,206,"And when it is said to him, \"Fear God,\" the pride of sin seizeth him: but he shall have his fill of Hell; and right wretched the couch"
  2,207,"A man, too, there is who selleth his very self out of desire to please God: and God is good to his servants"
  2,208,"O believers! enter completely into the true religion, and follow not the steps of Satan, for he is your declared enemy"
  2,209,"But if ye lapse after that our clear signs have come to you, know that God is Mighty, Wise"
  2,210,"What can such expect but that God should come down to them overshadowed with clouds, and the angels also, and their doom be sealed? And to God shall all things return"